name: Stonewall DayCare
description: The Stonewall staff is pleased to announce a new program to our families, “Parents Night Out”. This will occur on the third Friday of every month from 6:35pm-9:35pm. Stonewall must close (MSDE rule) at 6:30 and will reopen at 6:35 for the new program. Your child must leave Stonewall for dinner before returning for our fun filled night. A new sign-up sheet will be kept in the office beginning on the first of each month; sign up will close the Monday before the night out. We will have as many of our qualified teachers as it takes to keep within legal child/staff ratios. This will enable us to keep the evening a safe and happy place for your children. A list of rules is located on the next page. These rules are in addition to Stonewall policies and procedures. We will be strict in enforcing each and every one of them.
